      • mailChecker

        public static java.lang.Boolean mailChecker​(java.lang.String email)
        Email checker that controls the email passed as parameter. If the regex confirms it, function returns true the password should have at least: 1 character before @ a @ 1 character after @ a . after @ 2 characters after .
        Parameters:
        email - email to control with regex
        Returns:
        true if mail format is correct else false

      • passwordChecker

        public static java.lang.Boolean passwordChecker​(java.lang.String password)
        Password checker that controls the email passed as parameter. If the regex confirms it, function returns true the password should have at least: 1 uppercase letter 1 lowercase letter 1 number 6 characters in total no symbols
        Parameters:
        password - password to control with regex
        Returns:
        true if mail format is correct else false

      • siglaChecker

        Returns:

      • birthDateChecker

        public static java.lang.Boolean birthDateChecker​(java.time.LocalDate birthDate)
        Controls if the age of the user is between 16 and 90 otherwise
        Parameters:
        birthDate - birthdate to control
        Returns:
        true if the age of the subscriber between 16 and 90
        Throws:
        UtenteException - with TOO_OLD exception if age greater than 90
        UtenteException - with TOO_YOUNG exception if age less than 16

      • utenteFieldsChecker

        public static void utenteFieldsChecker​(UtenteDTO utenteDTO)
        Checks if the param is not null and the needed fields are valid, otherwise
        Parameters:
        utenteDTO - to control
        Throws:
        UtenteException - with MISSING_PARAMETERS exception
        UtenteException - with INVALID_MAIL if mail is not valid
        UtenteException - with INVALID_PASSWORD if password is not valid
        UtenteException - with INCONSISTENT_SIGLA if sigla is not valid
        See Also:
        mailChecker(String), passwordChecker(String), siglaChecker(Integer)
